The 'leek' is a vegetable that belongs, along with onion and garlic, to the
genus [[Allium]], currently placed in family Amaryllidaceae, subfamily
Allioideae.<ref></ref> Historically many scientific names were used for
leeks, which are now treated as cultivars of [[Allium ampeloprasum]].<ref
name="WCSP_294972"></ref> Two related vegetables, elephant garlic and
kurrat, are also cultivars of A. ampeloprasum, although different in
their uses as food.

The edible part of the leek plant is a bundle of leaf sheaths that is sometimes
erroneously called a [[plant stem|stem]] or stalk.
